text: Pyhäntä is a municipality in Northern Ostrobothnia, Finland. As of 31 December 2023, 1,646 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Kajaani, Kiuruvesi, Kärsämäki, Pyhäjärvi, Siikalatva, and Vieremä. It was founded in 1899. == Other websites == * Municipality of Pyhäntä – Official website Category:Municipalities of North Ostrobothnia Category:1899 establishments in Europe Category:1890s establishments in Finland
